        "executive_summary": "HOGONC's February 2026 performance reflects a network finding its footing, with two clinics demonstrating meaningful momentum while others face distinct operational headwinds. Our composite performance sits at an average of 42.75 out of 100 (where 50 represents the network average), associated with strong gains in scheduling compliance and chair utilization at NH MO and BCC MO, but offset by persistent delays and underutilization challenges at MTH MO and PW MO.",
        "highlights": [
          "NH MO has emerged as our clearest turnaround story, with scheduler compliance climbing 24.4 percentage points from 42.3% in January to 66.7% in February, while chair utilization rose 24.5 percentage points from 45.2% to 69.7% over the same period. BCC MO similarly strengthened its scheduling discipline, improving from 47.0% compliance in January to 67.1% in February\u2014a 20.1 percentage point jump\u2014and simultaneously boosted iAssign utilization from 76.2% to 95.0%, alongside chair utilization rising from 76.6% to 95.2%. Both clinics are approaching or meeting company benchmarks on core operational metrics, and BCC MO's chair utilization of 95.2% now sits 24.2 percentage points above the company average of 71.04%, reflecting disciplined capacity management."
